cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Network Functions Virtualization (NFV) in Software Defined Networks (SDN) and their deployment in multi-domain setups. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper addresses the problem of optimizing the deployment of virtual network functions (VNFs) with respect to energy consumption and Quality of Service (QoS) requirements. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with the deployment of VNFs across multiple SDN domains. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses evolutionary optimization algorithms to solve the VNF deployment problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on programming languages, but rather on the deployment of VNFs in SDN-enabled NFV setups.
